caption: This is definitely one of my favorite places to visit in Chinatown. Located on the second floor above Joyee, this hidden gem offers a ton of variety from boba, ice cream, cakes, shave ice and more. The interior is very trendy and has many spots for cute pictures. I’d recommend any of the mango items here because the mangos are perfectly ripe and sweet. We tried the water melon and mango seasonal item and it was perfect for an after dinner dessert because it was refreshing and not too heavy. I will be back here to try more things on the menu like the pancakes and cakes. If you are ever in Chinatown check out this place.
I am from Europe and wanted a best and unique desert place. I loved this place very much.its very  festive and service and flavours were so great.

We passed by this place and decided to try it. It’s super cute, love the theme, and their dessert were really good. We tried a few different ones and our favorite was the mango and coco crepes cakes. They also have combos paired with tea. Definitely recommend it on our next visit to Chinatown.
Spectacular
Always craving mango mango. Everything I've tried here is good. Obviously don't come here if you don't like mangos.
I got the strawberry mango.. it was watery and I personally did not like it. The waffles though were really good
The staff was pretty nice. I really liked the decor and choice of colors. The desserts were good too but not exceptional.

The place had a nice ambiance. They had this mango chaor for picture purposes, which did not seem super sanitary to me due to covid. I think they should of kept disinfectant wipes by the chair. The crepe was good. We also got 2 desserts with glutinous rice. The rice balls were super stale and old which was a dissapointment. Ither than that, the taste was good. Probably will not go back.
Delicious desserts and huge portions!
At last I found a HK style mango sweet shop in Chicago. And it’s not overly sweet.  This is a place I will go back over and over again.

Order an avocado cheese tea, strawberry mochi, mango tea and coco crepe roll. The tea had a nice earthy and sweet flavor similar to match. The crepe roll was a delicious dark chocolate with whipped cream on the inside. The mochi was not my favorite, I would definitely pick an ice cream mochi over this one. And the mango tea had good flavor.
This is definitely a hidden gem in the China  town square. A very cute place with delectable and innovative dishes from mango slushies to durian pancakes.
They welcome their customers til the very last minute. Very clean! They're following the Covid guidelines. Needless to say, the mango smoothie smacked 😭🔥
This place has my heart ❤️ truly a heaven for mango lovers. Their portions are a bit small for the prices but who’s complaining because everything on the menu is soooo soooo good. Highly recommended.

This place is adorable. We got the waffle with ice cream, fruit, whipped cream & chocolate syrup. It was a little undercooked so it tasted a little doughy but it was good for the most part. People who work here are nice so I'd definitely give them another shot and try something different next time. Its upstairs in case you can't find it.
Extremely good desserts!
Really nice place and desserts are delicious! If you love Mango you should definitely come here!!!
Great desserts. Not too sweet. Healthy combinations.
Really good. Clean, nice staff 👍
Mango pancake is the best!!
I love everything!!! All the drinks they have are amazing Sadly it would be 5 stars but they don't accept debit card or credit. Only cash

As the name would suggest, the mango desserts here are extremely good. The mangoes used taste fresh and sweet.  We also had the Ube Mozzarella Pancake, which is one of the best pastries we've had anywhere. The sign says it's seasonal but I hope they keep it forever!
The place so cute and everything is yummy. They currently have new items as well, so go explore those as well. The staff was very nice and they accept cash and card here.

I came here a while back after dinner in Chinatown.  It's also located in Chinatown, or just on the outskirts.  If you like mangos, this is a great place for dessert, that's all I have to say!  The dessert option are wide and I had an ice cream dessert with fresh mangos that was absolutely delicious.  The space is small but nice.  Very clean.  Service was friendly and very prompt.  I'm not sure I would go out of my way to come here again, but next time I'm in Chinatown, I will come here for dessert without any hesitation whatsoever.
Awesome desserts!!
Great place to satisfy a mango craving!
Good selection of mango and durian desserts.
This dessert shop reminds me of the ones in Hong Kong. Reasonably priced with larger portions.  Plus, where else in the city are you going to get so many durian-flavored options?
Such a cute Instagrammable spot! Stays open late so great for folks who don't drink and just want a nice place hangout. Free wifi! Great and interesting desserts. Definitely will be back.
Very spacious and comfortable! Loved the food and drinks
This place is new and clean! They have a very cute and quiet  atmosphere that's great place for a first date. I think it's a bit pricey for the portion you get, but the quality is good.
Awesome deserts! And very nice design!
Such a cute and neat place.  Staff were super polite.
The desserts are cute but very pricy. I love mangos so I can't help it. They also offer durian dishes so the place smells a bit like durian when you walk in but it's just food
Fun refreshing Asian desserts and drinks. Kinda pricey but very cute inside
My go-to mango dessert place 💛
More delicious than I ever thought!
Great desserts!! A must try if you're in Chinatown.

This place caught my eye with their design, that is pretty. Yet I didn’t like anything here but tea. Why wouldn’t you mention it in the menu if the main component of all your dishes is whipped cream??? Which doesn’t even taste like a homemade one... Banana nutella crepe has anything about Nutella at all, guys, chocolate toppings is not Nutella!!! Why a huge layer of whipped cream there?! Wasting of money. Just because of that I’m not gonna be back here. I hate whipped cream, please put it in your menu!!!
Love this place. Everything is mango related 😂 and the store is beautiful. Great place for a healthy sweet treat.
So tasty cakes n ice creams

Mango mango is usually good. Mangos are fresh and the ice cream is creamy but not too sweet. The pancakes have smooth cream with mango at the bottom and the crepe is amazing. I did have one visit where the mango was not the freshest though and I could taste it, but other than the one time it's always fresh.
Super cute shop for mango and fruit desserts!! Loved all the decor. We split one dessert bc we came after a full meal. It was light & refreshing. Would love to try a combo next time.

Just a general warning, if you don't like the smell of durian, it's here. I love the stuff but it's scent isn't for everyone. I brought my friends to eat some of the mango, pomelo, masago dessert. We got the A3 and A2. I personally like the ones without the white sauce because it retains more of the mango flavoring. This is my go to place for this dessert. I would like to try the crepe cakes and the durian versions but maybe by myself. Only thing I'd wish for is a little more mango in it.
Lots of mango in my mango, delicious
Kind of a hidden spot in Chinatown if you dont know about it.  Very good and light dessert but is often packed on weekends

(Translated by Google) There are many seats, a pretty cafe to take pictures, um ....... It's too expensive compared to Shenyang I ordered strawberry mango juice sago & lychee jelly with mango ice cream. $ 7 .... yes. It's enough to go once ...  (Original) 📎자리가 많은편, 사진 찍기 예쁜 카페, 음................. 📎양에 비해 가격이 너무 비싼거 같아서 두명이서 먹기에는 그나마 적당할듯 📎저는 strawberry mango juice sago& lychee jelly with mango ice cream 을 시켰는데.. 7달러....네....그냥 저냥 맛은 기본은 합니다... 📎음 한번 간것을 족해요...그럼 이만
Forgot what’s this called on the menu, but I ordered additional black rice so it looks a little bit different. busy days can be hard to find seats.
No need to come :)

This place is amazing the ice cream is delicious. Service was fast and friendly and located near the train station if you prefer to talk the train here. If you're driving there's free and paid parking
This is over all score, some of their food (or lot of) are not that good.

They have small bowls of shaved and creamy ice for $7 kinda pricey for the portion so docked a star off but I absolutely recommend the green tea with red bean and black rice smoothie/slushie for $5 it was the best! Liked it way better than the mango bowl. I would return just for the green tea slushie

The picture is durian bowl which tastes great if you love durian. The durian green pillow is good if you love a ton of creammm! I've tried all their thousand layered cake and they're all good.  But the best and my most favorite is still their classic mango smoothie with mango jelly and more. It's the BEST! I'm so addicted to it!

West coast chain finally arrived in the Midwest!  Yes everything is mango look at the posted photos there’s so much to choose from. Be bold and order the black sesame pudding with peanut mochi. Hard to find that dessert in Chinatown so I will go to MM when I crave it. Great customer service. If you dine in bring your tray to the counter when you’re done. Always busy as it’s a popular dessert spot. Prices are moderate but hey they only serve dessert so they have to be able to pay rent and staff.
It fun and yummy come with friends, family or even alone and you will have a great time!

Delicious mango treats! Authentic taste from Hong Kong! The place was packed on weekends and night, but service was prompt and smooth. The food came quickly and was delicious. The durian pancake was full of light fluffy cream and a small piece of fresh durian. The mango sago was good with fresh mango and grass jelly. Credit accepted, validated parking, busy during weekends, might be hard to find seats

There's a saying in Asia. "By looking at the decorations and cleaness of restaurant washroom you can judge which class the restaurant belong in". The Mango Mango is definitely in fancy higher class of its own when compared with other restaurants in area. Washroom was not only decorate nice but also cleaned.  Dessert was beautiful and delicious. Worker was cheerful and helpful in helping customer to choose wonderful desserts. It was difficult to find this place for first timer.
Food & drink: 7/10 Service: 7/10 Decor & atmosphere: 7/10 Service speed: 6/10 Cost: 7/10  The best: Drinks are made well. The worst: Basic service  Insta: @bmjteh

The ice cream here was deliciousss. 11/10. Honestly one of the best sweet treats I've had in a long while. The atmosphere was nice and the staff were very kind and helpful. The prices were a little bit expensive but definitely worth the money. If I ever stop by Chinatown, I'll definitely stop by and grab some of their shaved mango ice cream again!😋
I love durian but the durian dessert bowl here is awful. Frozen durian has no taste at all
Probably one of the better shaved ice in the city. The durian desserts are sublime.
Great Chinese deserts
I think it was a-okay. Would be nice for fruity dessert lovers. They also have mochi, icecream, and other things. Not super sure if it's someplace I would want to visit again.
both are delicious!
Love this place. Their menu is overwhelming but the staff is super friendly and helpful. It’s generally pretty noisy but it’s not a big deal. Great place for a snack or dessert.

This place is awesome, try the B combo, especially the dessert with mini gluten balls! Great quality mango desserts at a decent price.  They use fresh mangos in all the dishes and you can definitely taste it. The portions are a bit small or maybe I could just eat it forever.  There is a decent amount of seating and staff are nice. It is located on the 2nd story for those that can't find it.  Looking forward to coming here again!

I LOVE MANGOES. The decor of this place is super cute and the seating is comfortable. Even on a weekday night, the place was filled! When we walked in, I immediately smelled durian. Two of us shared the mango juice with watermelon and rice ball, which was more so shaved ice - half watermelon and half mango, topped with watermelon, mango, and rice balls. This was absolutely delicious and a perfect treat in the warm summer. We also decided to order the mango pancakes because we saw a bunch of people with them. These aren't really worth it. They're essentially a piece of mango topped with whipped cream wrapped in a thin, smooth crepe. Can't wait to return!

Mango overload was what I got when I ordered the famous mango shaved ice (dine-in only). From the picture on the menu, does not give the size of this dish justice - I had sticker shock when the cashier said $15 until I saw it live. The shaved ice was like a mountain with 1 oz chunks of mango layered on it. Enough spoons for 4-5 people.  Overall the dish was not overly sweet but just right. I would recommend coming here on off-peak hours.
Amazing food. The one thing I missed was coffee.
The place is very clean and the presentation of each dessert is simple but nice. I recommend this place the desserts are good.
Nothing special, maybe I expected too much since it hasn’t been opened. Small portion against the price.

Long lines and packed on weekends, just to taste some of the delicious and delightful mango desserts, so good! Must visit in Chinatown! Latest desserts, Hong Kong style. You'll be back for more, especially the durian desserts. Be warned, hold your nose! But you will savor every bit of it, clean the dish.
Mango was fine, we preferred the snow white dessert with red beans and herbal jelly. Pricey for what you get.
Omg it was soo good. Their mango was really  ‏ delicious I was full so I could’t try more options,but definitely I’m gonna come again. Their decorations so pretty
Mango dessert was a good portion, too small to share, but good for individual. The mango was naturally sweet and light in combination with the snow white which gave it a much needed creaminess.

The staff were very friendly. The food was served promptly, though the plate seem like it did not fit steadily enough on their wooden trays. The appearance and the taste of the food was excellent, and they used great mangoes.

We went to this new dessert place about two weeks ago. It’s located on 2nd floor across MingHin. We tried Mango Mango when we were in Dallas, so we we were excited knowing they opened a store in Chicago. First impression the moment I entered the restaurant, the durian smell was very strong. I know some people love durian, but I don’t. The strong smell of durian really bothered me the entire time we were in the restaurant.  The menu has plenty of selections, mostly everything with mangoes. I noticed there are some asian desserts as well like black sesame porridge, etc. We ordered two desserts, basically they were the same, just different toppings (grass jelly n mochi). Like some reviewers, I agree the price is quite high for such a small serving.  Overall: Menu: 4stars Price: $ Food: 4stars Service: 4stars  It’s ok...
Really tasty desserts
Fun dessert spot!
The taste is fair but is expensive against its size. The place is too crowded and noisy in my opinion.
Mango pancake. Not what u normally think for pancake but was delicious. The slushie bowl just tasted like a regular smoothie with mangos but the quality was good

Nothing too special. The mango was very sweet so that was good but it was quite expensive for not a lot of dessert. The mango sago with herbal jelly was $6.50. The decor was pretty cute but blasting music so I couldn't even clearly hear the workers.
So good🍮🍰🍧
Finally find a Hong Kong style dessert in Chinatown. Everything is awesome! Mango mango is must be my go-to
(Translated by Google) The dessert shop that has been waiting for a long time has finally opened. It’s really delicious to taste it in the past.  (Original) 期待了好久的甜品店终于开门了 过去尝了一下真的很好吃啊
Best dessert I’ve had in Chicago!!! love it.

A different type of dessert shop. Their menu is different, you will find mango in most of the desserts in menu, low in sugar and a different taste. We were a group of 8 people and everyone liked the dessert they ordered here.
